main event: Two witnesses observed two bright bluish white lights hovering and moving at extreme speeds near Cincinnati, Ohio on January 23, 1968.
interesting points: The lights were reported to hover and then move off to the southeast after about 30 minutes of observation,The lights were similar in appearance to airplanes but lacked usual aircraft lights,The observation included unusual behavior such as changing positions and disappearing suddenly, Lockbourne AFB reported no radar contact with the objects at the time of the sighting, Witnesses included deputies and residents who described the lights as glowing and pulsating.
witness description: deputies and civilians in the area
